# sol-edge-os — Phase 10D execution credentials
#
# Copy this file to .env (already gitignored — never commit a real .env)
# and fill in real values only when actually running mode="live" in
# config/execution.json. paper and shadow modes never read these.
#
# REQUIRED EXCHANGE KEY PERMISSIONS:
#   - Trade-only. Withdrawals MUST be disabled on the exchange's API key
#     management page for this key. There is no code-level substitute for
#     this — it is an exchange-side setting and must be set there.
#   - Do not reuse a key that has withdrawal permission elsewhere; create
#     a fresh, scoped key for this runtime.
#
# These two vars are also listed in config/execution.json's
# live.requiredEnvVars — the runtime refuses to start in live mode unless
# both are present in the environment, in addition to liveConfirmed=true
# in that same file. Neither check alone is sufficient.

EXCHANGE_KEY=
EXCHANGE_SECRET=
